    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-01-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 15,
                            1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan replies to the telegram of the 13th, and says that the fiscal
                        analyzes at great length Johnson’s and Langan’s sworn testimony, which shows
                        that a policeman fired at close range the rifle which killed Riggin, and
                        throws it out, in its entirety, as conflicting; that the same officer
                        ignores the evidence of the officers and surgeon of the <hi rend="italic">Baltimore</hi> and the circumstance of Johnson’s tie and shirt being
                        pierced by a bullet, and arrives at the conclusion that Riggin’s death was
                        caused by a revolver shot.</p>
            </div>
